<HEADLINE> Pakistan In Grip Of Cold Wave </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is in the grip of a
cold wave with temperatures dropping below the freezing point
following rains and snowfall.
</P>
<P>
According to local media reports, the minimum temperature in
Murree, about 100 km east of here, fell to -4.1 centigrade, after
it received 20.3 mm of snowfall.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, the cold weather was experienced in the Federal
capital with the temperature going down to 5.5 centigrade while in
Quetta, capital of Balochistan Province, it remained -3
centigrade.
</P>
<P>
The Northern Areas have also been undergoing a severe cold wave
for the last week, paralyzing normal life.
</P>
<P>
The snowfall and intermittent rains in most parts of Northern
Areas forced people to stay indoors and hampered the business
activities on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
