<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Congratulates CPV Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, General
Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China, Monday congratulated Le Kha Phieu on his election as
General Secretary of the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV).
</P>
<P>
In a letter, General Secretary Jiang Zemin warmly
congratulated Le's election.
</P>
<P>
"We notice that since the 8th National Congress of the CPV
the overall reform and socialist construction cause of Vietnam
have moved forward," noted Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"We are pleased to see the friendly cooperative ties between
the two parties and two countries have been cemented since the 8th
congress," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"We believe Vietnam will achieve its goals set at the 8th
congress, and the traditional China-Vietnam friendship will be
further strengthened in the future," he added.
</P>
<P>
Le Kha Phieu, 66, was elected CPV general secretary at its 4th
plenary session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
