<HEADLINE> US Jet Hit Air Turbulence, Killing One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 28 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 passengers
aboard a United Airlines jumbo jet were injured and one was killed
when the U.S. plane hit massive air turbulence over the Pacific
late Sunday.
</P>
<P>
United Flight 826 was en route to Honolulu when it encountered
severe turbulence and returned to Narita international airport,
which is about 64 kilometers away from Tokyo, a spokesman of the
United Airlines said from the company's Chicago headquarters.
</P>
<P>
At least 74 passengers and nine flight attendants were taken to
Tokyo hospitals, the spokesman said. All except nine passengers
and one flight attendant were treated and released. The passenger
who was killed was a Japanese woman.
</P>
<P>
The Boeing 747 plane, carrying 393 passengers and 19 crew
members, left Narita at 9:15 p.m. local time and turned after
about two hours into the air, landing back in Narita at
2:20 a.m. Monday, the airline said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
