<HEADLINE> New Romanian Foreign Minister Approved by Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian Parliament
Monday approved the appointment of Andrei Plesu as foreign
minister of the country.
</P>
<P>
Plesu, 49, was nominated last Tuesday when his predecessor
Andrian Severin was forced to resign because of his unsupported
allegations that some heads of the nation's political parties and
newspapers were spys of foreign counties.
</P>
<P>
After accepting the nomination by Severin's Democratic
Party, a procedure agreed upon by the ruling parties, Plesu
said he would remain independent in the foreign minister's office.
</P>
<P>
Plesu was Cultural Minister in the first Romanian government
after the political changes in 1989 and stepped down at the end of
1991 to teach philosophy in the Bucharest University. 
</P>
</TEXT>
