<HEADLINE> CPV 4th Plenary Session Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The 4th plenary session of
the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV) ended here Monday, electing
a new leader and passing a resolution calling for furthering the
country's reforms.
</P>
<P>
The session stressed that Vietnam should continue the
renovation process, bring into full play internal strength,
enhance international cooperation, practice thrift and work hard
towards industrialization and modernization in order to meet the
target set by the party's 8th congress for the rest of this
century.
</P>
<P>
It also called for unity of the party, the army and all
Vietnamese citizens, and agreed that Vietnam should grasp the
historic opportunity to carry a prosperous nation into the new
century.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the achievements gained during the past two years,
the plenum said they once again proved that the party and
state's orientation and policy were correct.
</P>
<P>
At the week-long plenum, Le Kha Phieu, 66, was elected CPV
general secretary to succeed 81-year-old Do Muoi.
</P>
<P>
Do, along with former president Le Duc Anh and former prime
minister Vo Van Kiet, also left the politburo to become advisors
to the Party Central Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
