<HEADLINE> Greece's Corinth Canal to Remain Closed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Greece's Corinth Canal would
remain closed for another week for repairs, the canal authority
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The canal, which connects central Greece with the Peloponnese
peninsula, was damaged by landslides nearly two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
The waterway, 6.3 kilometres long and 7 metres deep, was
completed in 1893. 
</P>
</TEXT>
