<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkmenistan-Iran Pipeline Starts Operating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Turkmen President Saparmurad
Niyazov and Iranian President Sayed Mohammad Khatami today took
part in a ceremony in Ashgabat on the occasion of opening the
natural gas pipeline from Turkmenistan to Iran, the Interfax news
agency reported from Ashgabat, Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
The natural gas pipeline from Korpedzhe in Turkmenistan to Kord
Kuy in northern Iran began operating Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 200-kilometer pipeline beginning in 1998 will deliver about
4 billion cubic meters of Turkmen gas to Iran, rising to about 8
billion cubic meters by 2006, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Iran has guaranteed to purchase Turkmen gas for the next 25
years.
</P>
<P>
This pipeline is seen as a segment of a wider project to build
a gas pipeline from Turkmenistan to Europe via Iran and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Last Sunday a tripartite agreement between Turkmenistan, turkey
and Iran on the construction of the gas pipeline was signed by
their state ministers in Ashgabat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
