<HEADLINE> Nyerere in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Former Tanzanian President
Julius Nyerere arrived here today to pay a three-day surprise
visit to Zambia amid speculations that he came here to mediate a
release of detained former President K. Kaunda.
</P>
<P>
When asked if his visit is related to detention of Kaunda,
Nyerere did not deny or say "yes".
</P>
<P>
He was greeted at the airport by three Zambian ministers
including Foreign Minister Keli Walubita.
</P>
<P>
Nyerere is expected to have private talks with Zambian
President Frederick Chiluba.
</P>
<P>
The post newspaper of Zambia today quoted diplomatic sources
in Dar es Salaam of Tanzania as saying that southern African
presidents are to approach Nyerere to intercede with the Zambian
government to secure the release from detention of Kaunda.
</P>
<P>
The initiative is reported to be spearheaded by South African
President Nelson Mandela in consultation with Ketumile Masire of
Botswana, Joachim Chissano of Mozambique, Robert Mugabe of
Zimbabwe, Sam Nujoma of Namibia and Benjamin Mkapa of Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Kaunda was arrested last Thursday allegedly in connection with
the October 28 abortive coup. He returned home last Monday after
a marathon overseas trip, which took him to India, South Africa,
Zimbabwe, the United States and Britain among other countries.
</P>
<P>
He went abroad on the eve of the coup to seek international
pressure on the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
