<HEADLINE> Life Hotline Callers Increase in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 30 (Xinhua) -- More people in Macao are calling
a hotline offering counseling service on family issues, personal
relationship and love, the Va Kio newspaper reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
There have been more than 3,000 calls for help at the Life
Hotline run by the Macao Charity so far this year, up about 400
from last year.
</P>
<P>
Most of the callers said they were troubled with unemployment
and love affairs, said the report. The number of callers seeking
help on mental problems also rose considerably.
</P>
<P>
Macao has seen a sluggish economy for the third year running,
and the unemployment rate was recorded at three percent in the
August-October period this year, with the number of jobless at
about several thousand.
</P>
<P>
To cope with the increasing callers, a spokesman for the Macao
Charity said that the organization plans to add more volunteers
for the hotline next year.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that we will not only listen, but we also want to go
out and help," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The hotline has been running for a decade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
