<HEADLINE> Chinese, South African Foreign Ministers Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(by Liu Yegang, Zhao Yi)
</P>
<P>
PRETORIA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen today held talks
with South African Foreign Minister Alfred Nzo in the Union
Building, Pretoria, with the two sides pledging to promote
bilateral cooperation after the establishment of diplomatic
relations between the two countries as of January 1.
</P>
<P>
Nzo told reporters after the meeting that it is great honor
for him to sign with Qian a joint communique on the establishment
of diplomatic relations between South Africa and China.
</P>
<P>
He said the establishment of South Africa-China diplomatic
relations will lay a solid foundation for the development of
bilateral relations in the future.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's decision to normalize its relations with China
is in line with international diplomatic norms and the "one China
policy" implemented by the majority of countries in the world, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
South Africa shared its viewpoints with China in establishing
fair international political and economic new order, with the two
sides making efforts to safeguard the rights and interests of
developing countries, Nzo said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that cooperation between South Africa
and China on internatioanl issues will be developed.
</P>
<P>
In response, Qian Qichen spoke highly of the decision by South
African President Nelson Mandela and his government to sever
official ties with Taiwan and establish diplomatic relations with
China.
</P>
<P>
Qian said the establishment of Sino-South African diplomatic
relations favors the fundamental interests of the peoples of the
two countries, and serves as an important milestone in the development
of Sino-South African relations.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that China and South Africa, both important
developing countries in their respective continents, have no
conflict of interests but comprehensive common interests.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are economically complementary with great
potentialities of cooperation in various fields, including
trade, science and technology and culture.
</P>
<P>
Qian said the peoples of the two countries had been supporting
each other in the struggle against apartheid, which laid solid
foundation for the establishment of the new relations, friendship
and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said China attaches importance to the development of
relations with South Africa and expects to turn the current
bilateral relations more vigorous.
</P>
<P>
Qian invited Nzo to visit China at his convenience. Nzo
pleasingly accepted the invitation.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Qian and Nzo also introduced the economic
development in their respective countries, and exchanged
viewpoints on international problems and issues of mutual
concern.
</P>
<P>
China's Deputy Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation Shi Guangsheng and Assistant Foreign Minister Ji
Peiding, and South African Deputy Foreign Minister Aziz Pahad
participated in the talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
