economic restructuring, hasten infrastructure construction,
provide more job opportunities for rural and urban workers and
improve both the quality and performance of its national economy
next year, said Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
During an inspection from Dec. 26 through today, Zhu, also a
member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the
Communist Party of China the Central Committee, visited Hubei,
Jiangxi and Guangdong provinces along the Beijing-Kowloon Railway,
extending greetings and solicitude to local farmers and workers.
</P>
