<P>
DHAKA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Italian Prime Minister Romano
Prodi will pay a two-day visit to Bangladesh from January 8 to
enhance relations between the two countries, the national news
agency BSS reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first time that an Italian head of government
pays an official visit to Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Prodi will hold talks with his Bangladeshi
counterpart Sheikh Hasina on bilateral relations, and regional and
international issues of mutual concern. He is also expected to
meet President Shahabuddin Ahmed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
