<HEADLINE> Public Forum on Legislature Election Guidelines Held in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Electoral Affairs
Commission of Hong Kong held a forum here on Tuesday to hear the
public's views on proposed guidelines for the Legislative Council
election.
</P>
<P>
The 17-chapter draft guidelines on election-related activities
for the Legislative Council general election next May and the
Election Committee subsector election next April was released by
the commission on December 18 for a two-week public consultation.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's forum held at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center included two sessions, one in the morning, and the other in
the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
During the two sessions chaired by Justice Woo Kwok-hing,
chairman of the Electoral Affairs Commission, local citizens
including representatives from various sectors actively raised
their views and suggestions on a range of issues such as polling
station arrangement, voting systems and qualification for voters.
</P>
<P>
Woo said: "we shall carefully consider all representations
before making regulations related to electoral procedures and
finalizing the guidelines."
</P>
<P>
The revised guidelines are expected to be published in February
next year.
</P>
<P>
The 60-member Legislative Council will be made up of 20 seats
to be returned from five geographical constituencies, 30 seats
from 28 functional constituencies and 10 seats from the 800-member
Election Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
