<HEADLINE> Large Ethylene Project in South China Operates Soundly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 30 (Xinhua) -- A 300,000-ton ethylene
project in Maoming City, south China's Guangdong Province, was
operating well this year, turning out 300,000 tons of ethylene by
December 29.
</P>
<P>
He Dexian, general manager of the Maoming Petrochemical Co.,
said today the production reached the designed amount in the
project's first year of formal operation, a new record in
China's ethylene industry.
</P>
<P>
Work on the project begun in November 1993, with more than
17 billion yuan (two billion US dollars) in investment. It went
into trial operation in August, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The general manager said that major technological indexes of
the project are leading the country, with high ethylene production
rate and low energy consumption.  
</P>
