<HEADLINE> Vietnam's New Leader Outlines New Policies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's new top leader Le Kha
Phieu today stressed that Vietnam will take the "self-sovereignty,
and self-determination" as the prime policies in the coming years.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks in a speech delivered at the closing
ceremony of the fourth plenary session of the Central Committee of
the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said Vietnam would mobilize to the utmost domestic resources
and at the same time attract outside resources in order to
accelerate the process of industrialization and modernization.
</P>
<P>
The country will also speed up the shifting of economic
structure and improving investment environment in a bid to raise
the efficiency and competitiveness of its economy.
</P>
<P>
Phieu emphasized that Vietnam would exercise stricter state
management over its economy while continuing to introduce market
factors.
</P>
<P>
He said Vietnam would pay more attention to agriculture and
farmers. More efforts would be put to the solving the problems of
land for farmers and promoting agricultural product sales and
establishing agricultural products processing industry.
</P>
<P>
He added that the country would try to balance the development
of the economy and promotion of social progress. It would
encourage people to become rich legally while paying more attention
to eradicating poverty.
</P>
<P>
He called for the whole party to effectively implement the
resolutions and new policies passed at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Phieu, 66, was elected CPV General Secretary to succeed
81-year-old Do Muoi at the week long session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
