<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Premier Calls For Steady, Healthy Development of Power Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China should boost development
of hydroelectric power by optimizing thermal power supply
structure while attaching importance to tapping new energy
resources, said Li Peng, premier of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a national power conference which ended here today,
Li Peng called on the staff workers in the country's power
industry to intensify reforms so as to maintain a steady and
healthy development.
</P>
<P>
The industry has achieved a fast growth in the past two
decades. As for seven years running, the large and medium-sized
generating units with the total capacity of more than 10 million
kw have been put into operation annually. The total power generating
capacity reached 250 million kw this year.
</P>
<P>
However, development of power industries in different regions
remains unbalanced even though a serious shortage of power
nationwide has been eased in recent years, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He urged the State Power Corporation of China (SP) to speed up
constructions of grids in order to make better use of hydropower
resources and coal, which are abundant in the west.
</P>
<P>
A national grid is going to take shape as regional grids in
eastern, northeastern, northern and central parts of China are
linked.
</P>
<P>
The corporation was asked to maintain a safe operation of the
national grid, as well as a fair and reasonable control of
electricity prices.
</P>
<P>
Overseas capitals should be used reasonably in the country's
power industry, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Attending today's conference included Wu Bangguo, vice premier
of the State Council, and Shi Dazhen, Minister of Electric Power
and general manager of SP.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
