<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expressway Opens for Traffic in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 30 (Xinhua) -- An expressway linking
Shijiazhuang, capital of Hebei Province, with Anyang City in north
China's Henan Province, was opened to traffic today.
</P>
<P>
Vice premier Zou Jiahua attended the ceremony marking the
completion of the 216-kilometer Shijiazhuang-Anyang Expressway,
which is part of a planned expressway linking Beijing and Zhuhai
in south China's Guangdong Province. To date 607 kilometers of the
expressway is open.
</P>
<P>
The Shijiazhuang-Anyang Expressway cost 4.65 billion yuan,
which includes 240 million U.S. dollars in loans from the World
Bank.
</P>
<P>
The expressway used 11 million tons of soot, a waste product
from coal-fired power plants in the region, and was praised by the
State Economic and Trade Commission for utilizing resources in an
optimal way. Soil from farmland formerly was used for the base of
expressways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
