<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quality of Huaihe River Approaches Drinking Water Standards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The water quality of the
Huaihe River's trunk stream is approaching drinking water
standards, according to the latest statistics from the China
Environment Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
This means that the drinking water problem of residents along
the river has been eased, experts said.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 78 percent of the seriously polluted sections have shown
remarkable water quality improvement, and the contents of organic
pollutants at 17 of the 18 major monitoring sites are equal to or
better than the standards set for drinking water.
</P>
<P>
East China's Anhui and Jiangsu provinces have shown the
greatest improvement.
</P>
<P>
The water in Xinyang Prefecture on the upper reaches of the
Huaihe River has reached reservoir standards, and so have some
sections in the middle and lower reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
Although the river valley has suffered from drought since June,
and water flow has decreased by a large margin, the pollution
problem still has been eased.
</P>
<P>
Experts with the monitoring center attribute the improvement to
efforts by major polluters in the valley. However, they warn that
the pollution situation is still serious, and more efforts are
still required.
</P>
<P>
All the factories in the Huaihe River Valley should meet
national wastewater emission standards by Dec. 31, according to
the requirements of the State Council, or face compulsory
closure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
