<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Emphasizes Open Village Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 30 (Xinhua) -- To build grassroots democracy
in rural areas is a key part of developing China's socialist
democracy, and the move is of vital significance to cement
relations between cadres and the masses, boost the rural reform,
development and stability, said Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks while looking into the management of
village affairs in some rural areas of Tianjin, a port city in
north China, from December 29 to 30.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said about 90 percent of villages in Tianjin
have implemented open village affairs and democratic management of
the public affairs.
</P>
<P>
Practices have shown that open village affairs and democratic
management have brought about many benefits, said Jiang Chunyun,
who elaborated that villagers have more say in village affairs,
and village leaders are looked over more effectively.
</P>
<P>
As a result, village leaders tend to grow more clean and
honest, diligent, amiable and democratic, and the relations
between villager leaders and the masses become closer, he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the report delivered by Jiang Zemin at the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China, grassroots
democracy will be improved and the people will be assured of
direct and democratic access to managing their own affairs so as
to bring about a happy life.
</P>
<P>
The system of open village affairs and democratic management is
popular among rural leaders and the masses, Jiang Chunyun said,
urging local officials to be fully aware of the importance and
necessity of conscientiously carrying out the system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
