<HEADLINE> HK's Re-exports, Imports Value Up in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
re-exports in November this year rose by 6.3 percent over a year
earlier to 106.7 billion HK Dollars (13.68 billion U.S. Dollars),
according to official figures released here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The figures issued by the Census and Statistics Department show
that the value of imports in the month grew by 1.5 percent over a
year earlier to 133 billion HK Dollars (17.05 billion U.S.
Dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, the value of Hong Kong's domestic exports stayed at 18
billion HK Dollars (2.3 billion U.S. Dollars), little change
compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
A visible trade deficit of 8.3 billion HK Dollars (1,064
million U.S. Dollars), equivalent to 6.3 percent of the value of
imports, was recorded in November, which was smaller than the
corresponding deficit of 12.6 billion HK Dollars (1,615 million
U.S. Dollars), equivalent to 9.6 percent of the value of imports
in November last year.
</P>
<P>
For the first 11 months of 1997, the value of total exports
rose by 3.9 percent over the same period last year and that of
imports registered an increase of 5.2 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
