<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese air carriers will
cancel nearly 3,700 flights on air routes with low passenger
loads, and add nearly 4,300 flights on heavily traveled routes
from Jan. 8 to Feb. 26 to prepare for the upcoming crunch during
Spring Festival.
</P>
<P>
The Spring Festival, the Chinese lunar new year, falls on
Jan. 28. Large numbers of college students and non-local employees
are expected to return home for family reunions during this period.
</P>
<P>
Major areas for heavy air traffic will be in the southern and
eastern parts of the country. The number of flights added for
Guangzhou, Shanghai, Shenzhen, Haikou, Beijing, Chengdu, Wenzhou,
Sanya, and Zhuhai will reach more than 3,500, accounting for 82.5
percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
The number of air travelers is expected to reach 7.6 million
during the holiday period, up from 7.25 million last year.
</P>
