<HEADLINE> HK Celebrates First IOI Gold Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Education Department of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of China held a party
today to celebrate the first gold medal won by the Hong Kong
team in the International Olympiad in Informatics (IOI) 1997.
</P>
<P>
Poon Wing-chi, who is now studying at the Hong Kong University,
won the first gold medal for Hong Kong in the IOI'97 held in Cape
Town, South Africa, from November 30 to December 7.
</P>
<P>
The IOI is an international contest organized by the United
Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization to
promote interest in computers among young people.
</P>
<P>
Some 200 secondary students participated in the Hong Kong
Olympiad in Informatics jointly organized by the Education
Department, the Hong Kong Association for Computer Education and
the Hong Kong Computer Society in March 1997.
</P>
<P>
Four of them were selected to represent Hong Kong in the IOI in
South Africa. The other three members of the Hong Kong team were
Lau Tsz-kit from La Salle College, Chung Wing-on from TWGHs Wong
Fut Nam College and Leung Chun-ho from Sing Yin Secondary School.
</P>
<P>
The Deputy Director of Education, Kwan Ting-fai, presented
souvenirs to the students and their teachers at the party.
</P>
<P>
The first IOI was held in Bulgaria in 1989. Since then, it was
held annually in different countries. Hong Kong took part in the
fourth IOI in 1992 for the first time.  
</P>
</TEXT>
