<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman on Military Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Tang Guoqiang said today that China will strictly
implement the regulations concerning management of the export of
military products.
</P>
<P>
With regard to projects and contracts for export, China will
issue export licenses only after completing careful examinations
on an individual basis, said Tang during at today' news conference.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese government has always taken a
"cautious and responsible" attitude toward and exercised
effective management of the export of military goods.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that the regulations, whose full text was carried in
People's Daily on November 3, define stipulations on management
departments and procedures.
</P>
<P>
He added that the regulations have also reiterated China's
general principle on the export of military products, standardized
trade activities by concerned trade companies, and defined
concrete measures related to the approval and management of the
export of such products, as well as punishment for violators.
</P>
