<HEADLINE> New Malaysian Army Chief Assumes Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 30 (Xinhua) -- General Mohd Zahidi
Zainuddin officially took over as Chief of Army of Malaysia
Tuesday from General Ismail Hassan who retires Wednesday after 36
years of military service.
</P>
<P>
In his inaugural order, the new Army Chief called on military
personnel to be sensitive to latest developments and responsive to
change.
</P>
<P>
Gen Mohd Zahidi Zainuddin, 49, was formerly Deputy Chief of
Army.
</P>
<P>
He was a student of the Royal Military College and entered
military service on April 13, 1968 as an officer with the Royal
Malay Regiment.
</P>
<P>
The new Army Chief told reporters that the country's current
economic slow-down enabled the Army to review its modernization
plans and the service will make the most of the slow-down to
concentrate more on human resource development.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian government has reduced the Defense Ministry's
current allocation by 700 million ringgit (181 million U.S.
dollars) as part of its austerity drive in the light of the
prevailing economic situation. 
</P>
