<HEADLINE> Presidency of Muslim-Croat Federation Transferred </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Vladimir Sholjich, president of
the Muslim-Croat Federation in Bosnia-Herzegovina, formally
transferred his power to vice president Ejup Ganich on Monday.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony for the transfer was held in Sarajevo, as decided by
the federation's parliament, and agreed on by Croats and Serbs.
</P>
<P>
Alija Izetbegovic, chairman of the Bosnian Presidency, its
Croat member Kresimir Zubak, and leaders of the Bosnia-Herzegovina
Republic were there for the event.
</P>
<P>
As provided by an agreement in 1994, when the Muslim-Croat
Federation was established, its president and vice president
should alternate between a Serb and a Croat.
</P>
<P>
Its first president was Zubak.
</P>
<P>
In September 1996, when Zubak became member of the Bosnian
Presidency and Muslim leader Izetbegovic its chairman, Croat
leader Sholjich resumed the Muslim-Croat Federation's presidency.
</P>
<P>
With the power transfer on Monday, Ganich became the first
Muslim president of the federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
