<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Coming mostly from Turkey and Iraq, 835 Kurds arrived on a
boat last Saturday in Italy for transition to Germany and Nordic
countries, where most of them have relatives. Their trip started
in Istanbul in the European consulates and then at the ticket desk
of the mafias specialized in "meat on foot," who charged 20,000 to
40,000 (3,300 to 6,600 U.S. dollars) for the trafficking of each
person. European authorities are afraid of more migration of the
Kurds, trapped in the war between the Turkish army and the PKK
guerrillas, which has resulted in the death of 25,000 people.
</P>
<P>
-- According to a document in the archive of the French army,
the Vichy collaboration regime of France during World War II had
ordered the internment of all Jewish soldiers serving in the
French army in North Africa, notably Algeria, deprived them of
their French nationality and sent them to southern Algeria to
build railways and other infrastructures.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The French government is studying a project to encourage
African immigrants to use their savings as productive investments
in their home country and ask French enterperises in Africa to use
their private fund in favor of aid projects for African countries,
as a way to check emigration to France. The government has also
found that the "aid for return" distributed to illegal immigrants
when they are returned home has not worked as an efficient way to
stop emigration.
</P>
<P>
-- The European consortium Airbus Industrie was approaching its
goal of obtaining half of world airspace market by winning 451
orders, as compared with 572 by the Boeing, in 1997, the best
result in its history. These orders amount to 185-190 billion
francs (32-33 billion U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
