<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Continue its All-Round Diplomacy Next Year: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China will continue to carry
out its independent foreign policy of peace in an all-round way
next year in accordance with the diplomatic thoughts of late
leader Deng Xiaoping and the strategic policy outlined at the 15th
National Conference of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang Guoqiang made the remarks at a
press conference here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He said China's foreign policy next year will serve to create a
long-term, sound international environment for the country's
socialist modernization program, a good neighboring environment in
particular, and to maintain world peace and promote joint
development.
</P>
<P>
China will implement the outcome of the China-ASEAN informal
summit and intensify the China-ASEAN good-neighborly and
mutual-trust partnership oriented towards the 21st century. China
will also enhance its unity and cooperation with the countries in
Africa, Latin America, south Asia, and central and east Europe and
strive to establish a just and rational international political
and economic order, Tang noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China will work still harder to implement the
outcome of President Jiang Zemin's trip to the United States and
do a good job in receiving President Clinton's upcoming China
visit, so as to further advance Sino-US relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
China will give full scope to the the role of the regular
meeting mechanism between the prime ministers of China and Russia
in an effort to further increase Sino-Russian cooperation in every
field, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the next year is the 20th anniversary of
the signing of Sino-Japanese Treaty of Peace and Friendship and
both sides will continue conducting high-level exchange of visits.
</P>
<P>
The momentum of high-level exchange of visits between China and
Western European countries will also be maintained, Tang noted.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China will continue to actively participate in the
multilateral diplomacy and play a constructive role in the issues
like the UN reform, regional conflicts, peace-keeping,
disarmament, arms control and environment protection, he stated.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue carrying out the policy of `one country, two
systems', maintaining Hong Kong's prosperity and stability, do
well the preparatory work for Macao's return to the motherland,
resolutely safeguard China's independence, sovereignty and
territorial integrity and advance the great cause of the
reunification of our motherland," the spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
