<HEADLINE> Sino-South African Relations Reach A Milestone (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The establishment of
diplomatic relations between China and South Africa represents a
milestone in bilateral relations, according to a senior Chinese
diplomat.
</P>
<P>
China's Assistant Foreign Minister Ji Peiding made the
statement during a recent interview with Xinhua News Agency and
China Central Television.
</P>
<P>
Ji said the establishment of diplomatic ties would enhance
solidarity and cooperation between China and nations in southern
Africa, as well as other developing countries.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of Sino-South African diplomatic relations is
of great significance, and friendship and cooperation between the
two countries will enter a new period of development, said Ji.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the establishment of Sino-South African diplomatic
relations will further reinforce solidarity and cooperation
between developing countries, and will at the same time promote
world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Ji noted that the establishment of diplomatic relations between
the two countries once again proves that attempts by Taiwan
authorities to create "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan" are
unpopular and run counter to world sentiment. Their "elastic and
pragmatic diplomacy" is doomed to failure, added Ji.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
