<HEADLINE> 30 Injured in Cricket Crowd Stampede </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- At least 30 people were
injured Tuesday when fans swarmed into a new stadium for a cricket
match, the United News of India said.
</P>
<P>
A 50,000-strong crowd gathered outside the stadium at
Puttaparthi in the southern state of Andhra Pradesh, the news
agency said.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the stampede occurred near the entrance gates
before the start of the one-day game, which was between an Indian
team and an International 11.
</P>
<P>
Only 30,000 had been expected for the match although the
stadium has a capacity of 100,000. 
