<HEADLINE> 25 Industrial Enterprises in Shanghai Become Bankrupt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-five industrial
enterprises have gone bankrupt and 45 others have been merged in
Shanghai this year.
</P>
<P>
According to government officials, 2.28 billion yuan in bad
loans were involved in these enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Of the 100,000 laid-off workers from these enterprises, 43,000
have retired, 34,000 are being trained at reemployment centers,
and many others have been employed by themselves.
</P>
<P>
A total of 83 industrial enterprises have gone bankrupt and 724
others have been merged in the city during the last four years. As
a result, 14.4 billion yuan of idle assets has been made better
use and the liability-asset ratio reduced from 80 percent
in 1994 to the present 60 percent, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The city government will step up efforts to encourage
legitimate bankruptcy and acquisition of industrial enterprises in
a bid to improve performance of the state-run industrial sector,
said the officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
