<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI -- A total of 37 Kenyans died of an unknown disease in
the past 24 hours in Wajir District, bringing the death toll to
more than 250 in the Northeastern Province this month.
</P>
<P>
The disease, earlier diagnosed by experts as severe malaria, is
also wiping out thousands of livestock, including camels, goats
and sheep, in the province, the Daily Nation newspaper reported
Tuesday. (Kenya-deaths)
