</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States could not impose sanctions on
Turkmenistan for its new gas pipeline to Iran, but it would be
looking closely at any feasibility studies for a proposed pipeline
from Turkmenistan to Turkey via Iran, the State Department said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
State Department spokesman James Foley said the Iran-Libya
Sanctions Act (ILSA), signed by President Bill Clinton in 1996 to
impose sanctions on any companies investing more than 20 million
dollars in either Iran's or Libya's energy sections, could not be
imposed on the gas pipeline between Turkmenistan and Iran,
inaugurated Monday, because the construction of the pipeline
predated the act. (US-Iran-Pipeline) 
</P>
