<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bridge Players Banned for Cheating with Pager </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Three players have been
suspended for cheating using a cellular phone and a pager during a
competition in September, the Chinese Bridge Association said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Tong of the Zhongjian Bridge Club in Beijing was banned
from the sport for five years, while Shi Zhengjun and Zhang Wenli,
both from the same club, suspended for three years, the
association said.
</P>
<P>
The trio were found cheating in the team-of-four event during
the 1997 National Bridge Tournament, said the competition's
Referee Committee chief He Jianguo.
</P>
<P>
He told Xinhua that Shi asked Zhang to call to pass vital card
information to Jiang through the paging service after Shi
completed his competition in the open room.
</P>
<P>
Jiang then knew the cards beforehand from his pager when he was
competing in the closed room, He said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
