<DOCNO> XIE19971230.0177 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Economy Grows 8.8 Percent (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China's gross domestic product
will reach 7,477.2 billion yuan this year, a rise of 8.8 percent
over last year, said Ye Zhen, spokesman for the State Statistics
Bureau, here today.
</P>
<P>
"The year 1997 witnesses China consolidating its achievements
in a soft landing for the national economy and making further
obvious progress in the overall economic control," commented Ye at
a press conference.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the Chinese economy grew 9.7 percent over 1995. As the
Chinese economic growth slows down, inflation in China is also
slipping lower.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's consumer price index and retails price
index are estimated to rise by 2.8 percent and 0.8 percent
respectively this year over 1996.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector is estimated to grow by 3.5 percent
this year, while the manufacturing and service sectors
by 10.8 percent and 8.2 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary estimates put China's grain output at 492.5 million
tons this year, the second year of bumper harvest in China's
history. Meanwhile, cotton output is to increase by 100,000 tons
to reach 4.3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
China's rape seeds output suffered a decrease of one million
tons to 21 million tons this year, as compared with last
year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
