<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ramos Calls on Filipinos to Rekindle Heroes' Spirit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos Tuesday called on the 70 million Filipinos to rekindle the
"selfless courage, sacrifice and vision" that national hero Jose
Rizal and his fellow martyrs bequeathed to the Filipinos.
</P>
<P>
Addressing on the 101th death anniversary of Rizal, Ramos said
it is important that "we reflect on Rizal's role in the collective
works, sacrifice and patriotic fervor exemplified by our heroes
and heroines during the crucial period of the revolutionary
struggle against the colonial government of Spain."
</P>
<P>
He said that one certain way of enabling the Filipino people to
imbibe the ideals and values of the heroes was by preserving the
sites and homes that stood as silent witnesses to their charting
the path to glory.
</P>
<P>
"Those shrines do not just commemorate the relevance they
played in our history but also serve as living centers of civic
consciousness and responsibility," he said after inaugurating the
newly rehabilitated Rizal Shrine at Fort Santiago in Intramuros,
Manila.
</P>
<P>
As a tribute to the patriots and unsung heroes who waged a
blazing trail to freedom from 1892 to 1898, the National
Centennial Commission set up four years ago has been busy in
developing and rehabilitating historical sites across the nation,
Ramos said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
