<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos Tuesday confirmed the reports that the opposition party, the
Nationalist People's Coalition (NPC), is negotiating with the
ruling Lakas-NUCD party for a possible merger in time for the May
1998 elections.
</P>
<P>
"We might say that at this stage, we are just talking just like
any couple that is courting," Ramos said, referring to the
possible merger to "a marriage of convenience."
</P>
