The NPC, headed by Senate President Ernesto Maceda, decided to
bolt the grand opposition union, the Laban Ng Makabayang Masang
Pilipino (LAMMP), after the LAMMP chose Vice President Joseph
Estrada and senator Edgardo Angara as running mates in next year's
presidential elections.
</P>
