<HEADLINE> Siemens to Expand Telecom Software Division in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The India-based software
division of the Siemens Public Communication Networks (SPCN) group
is all set to become the global electrical giant's major source
for telecom software, the Business Standard said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This follows a plan by SPCN to expand its Indian software
development center in Bangalore, an emerging industrial city in
southern India, while gradually reducing the current strength of
its other centers located in the United States, Austria and
Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Siemens Communication Software, Bangalore, part of the Siemens
Public Communication Networks Ltd, is a joint venture between
Siemens AG, Germany and Siemens Ltd India.
</P>
<P>
The Public Communication Networks group is the second largest
group within Siemens. The current expansion of its Indian center
is likely turn it to be the fastest growing software division of
the company.  
