<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) has agreed to provide 600,000 U.S. dollars to the Sri
Lanka-based Worldview International Foundation (WIF) for the
latter to produce video and radio programs on development issues
involving the poor, the official newspaper Daily News said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The non-governmental organization WIF will take the advantage
of the ADB fund to produce 52 video and 10 radio programs
featuring problems in the fields of education, health, population,
poverty reduction, women and children development and
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the programs are aimed at improving the
disadvantaged people's awareness on those issues as well as
promoting their active participation in related development
projects.
</P>
