The programs will also be used to inform the general public in
developing countries about the challenges and problems facing the
poor.
</P>
<P>
The WIF has already established its own educational network
Young Asia Television (YATV), which is broadcasting regularly in
Bangladesh, India, the Maldives, Nepal and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
It plans to soon expand broadcasting to Cambodia, Malaysia,
Pakistan, the Philippines, Thailand and Vietnam.  
