<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backbone Network Launched for Finance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The backbone network of the
China National Financial Network (CNFN), a key financial data
exchange network opened in Beijing on Monday, China Daily reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Bank officials were quoted as saying that construction of the
network marks an important step in computerizing the country's
financial industry.
</P>
<P>
The network was co-invested by the People's Bank of China
(PBOC), the Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications, the People's
Insurance Company of China and all Chinese commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
The CNFN now covers 200 cities around China and has a total
capacity of 2,500 trunks and user ports. It is expected to include
dozens of regional networks that are to provide safe, reliable and
convenient services to the financial industry.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the CNFN is of significant and decisive
importance to the development of the financial industry because it
can help speed up capital turnover and improve capital utilization
efficiency, said Shang Fulin, vice-governor of PBOC, the central
bank.
</P>
<P>
The network will also provide technical methods for the central
government to grasp the macro-financial situation and to improve
financial macro-control and supervision, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The China Financial Data Network Co Ltd, a company under the
PBOC launched at the beginning of this year, will take charge of
the construction, operation and management of the network.
</P>
<P>
To date, the Agricultural Bank of China, Bank of China, the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China, the China Everbright Bank
and two subsidiaries of the People's Insurance Company of China
have had access to the network.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that China's financial sector is intensifying
efforts to computerize as the robust development of the industry
demands such technical upgrading.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
