<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain to Expand Nature Preservation Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Spain declared on Monday that it
will expand the nature reserve from 8 percent of its land to 15
percent in the next few years.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made on the International Day of
Biological Diversity, which falls on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Spain possesses 1,500 biological varieties, or more than 50
percent of the total in Europe. statistics shows it has 74 percent
of the bird varieties and 79 percent of the mammal diversities of
Europe.
</P>
<P>
Forest fires and soil erosions have done damage to ecological
environment in Spain. The environmental protection department
was said to have worked out a strategy to be carried out next year.
</P>
</TEXT>
