<HEADLINE> Canadian Skater Improves World 1,000-m Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Canadian speed skater Jeremy
Wotherspoon clocked one minute, 10.16 seconds to improve men's
1,000-meter record in Calgary, Canada, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The mark set at the Canadian Olympic trials cut 0.26 seconds
off the previous record of 1:10.42 by South Korea's Lee Kyu-Hyuk
on the same ice last month.
</P>
<P>
Sylvain Bouchard was second as he was in the 500-meter to
qualify for the Canadian team to compete at the Winter Olympic
Games in Nagano, Japan, in February.
</P>
<P>
Two other spots will be decided at the second phase of the
trials to be held in January.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 1,000-meter, Catriona Le May Doan finished first
in 1:15.93. Susan Auch placed second and Linda Johnson Blair
third. 
</P>
