<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Economy Rises 8.8 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- China's gross domestic product
will reach 7,477.2 billion yuan in 1997, an increase of 8.8
percent over last year, Ye Zhen, spokesman for the State
Statistics Bureau, said here today.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector is estimated to grow by 3.5 percent
this year, while the manufacturing and service sectors by 10.8
percent and 8.2 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's grain output will be 492.5 million tons
this year, the second year of bumper harvest in China's
history. Meanwhile, cotton output is estimated to increase by
100,000 tons to reach 4.3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
China's rape seeds output suffered a decrease of one million
tons to 21 million tons this year, as compared with last year.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman puts China's estimate for its industrial added
value for 1997 at 3,175.2 billion yuan, a yearly increase of 11.2
percent. The industrial added value of the State-run industry is
estimated to grow 5.5 percent, roughly the same level as last
year's.
</P>
<P>
During the January-November period, China's 370,000 industrial
enterprises reaped a profit of 135.6 billion yuan, 19.6 percent up
from the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the profit of State-run enterprises was 34.2 billion
yuan, up 18 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
