<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Austria Outlines Tasks as Next EU Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Austria will give high priority
to the issues of the European single currency, environmental
protection and education when it chairs the European Union in the
second half of next year.
</P>
<P>
Austrian Foreign Minister Wolfgang Schuessel told the
newspaper, Kurier, that the most important job Austria would face
when it assumed the seat of the rotating chairman of the EU, was
to "carry out with great care the single currency program".
</P>
<P>
Nations which will join the single currency and a unified
exchange rate with other currencies will be decided on May 2, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The EU will put into effect higher standards of environmental
protection and an education program that will make the European
economic zone more appealing, said Schuessel, who also serves as
Austria's Vice Chancellor.
</P>
<P>
In the latter half of next year, Austria will also hold
substantive talks with the first group of countries applying for
EU membership, said Schuessel. The time to make a selection "will
be ripe" by then.
</P>
<P>
"Europe should appear on the international arena with a
friendly face and a strong voice," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
