rekindling hopes for a year-end rally as many traders returned
from Christmas holidays.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 113.10 points to
7,792.41, pushing this year's gain back above 20 percent with just
two sessions to go.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat Monday renewed a
call for deploying international peacekeepers in the West Bank to
secure peace between Israel and the Palestinian side.
</P>
<P>
According to Palestinian Radio Monday, Arafat said in Gaza that
under Israeli-Palestinian peace accords, international
peacekeeping forces should be deployed in the area, like those now
stationed in the West Bank city of Hebron.
</P>
<P>
Arafat raised the proposal when meeting with U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright in London on December 18. The Palestinian
National Authority on Saturday ratified this idea.
</P>
<P>
Arafat would set forth the proposal as part of his
comprehensive plan on the final settlement with the Israelis
during his coming talks with U.S. President Bill Clinton next
month in Washington.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S State Department on Monday confirmed that
Democratic Representative Tom Lantos had expressed his interest in
visiting Iran but was discouraged by the Clinton administration.
</P>
<P>
"He has expressed an interest in visiting Iran but let me
emphasize should he actually be traveling to Iran it would not be
at the request of the White House or the State Department," State
Department spokesman James Foley told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Monday, the White House denied a report from a Gulf
state's official news agency that Lantos had been sent by the
Clinton administration to Tehran in an effort to find any evidence
for the changes of Iranian foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
"We have no plans to send a special envoy to Tehran at all,"
White House spokesman Eric Rubin said. The reported visit was
"news to us," he added.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
HANOI -- The 4th plenary session of the Communist Party of
Vietnam (CPV) ended here Monday, electing a new leader and
passing a resolution calling for furthering the country's reforms.
</P>
<P>
The session stressed that Vietnam should continue the
renovation process, bring into full play internal strength,
enhance international cooperation, practice thrift and work hard
towards industrialization and modernization in order to meet the
target set by the party's 8th congress for the rest of this
century.
</P>
<P>
It also called for unity of the party, the army and all
Vietnamese citizens, and agreed that Vietnam should grasp the
historic opportunity to carry a prosperous nation into the new
century.
</P>
<P>
At the week-long plenum, Le Kha Phieu, 66, was elected CPV
general secretary to succeed 81-year-old Do Muoi.
</P>
<P>
----
