</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey said Monday that its military operations in
northern Iraq were aimed at eliminating the militants of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK).
</P>
<P>
"If there is a PKK existence in the region, the Turkish
government troops will not completely stop such operations there,"
Turkish Foreign Ministry spokesman Necati Utkan said at a weekly
press briefing.
</P>
<P>
The PKK rebels took advantage of the authority vacuum in
northern Iraq to attack Turkey, posing a serious threat to
Turkey's security, Utkan said.
</P>
<P>
But he assured Turkey's respect for the territorial integrity
of Iraq in the operations. 
</P>
