<HEADLINE> Ukraine's Prime Minister Extols China Experience </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Prime Minister Valery
Pustovoitenko was so impressed on his recent trip to China that he
is sending experts to Shanghai to learn about setting up free
economic zones.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing his trip, Pustovoitenko said on Monday that political
harmony is essential for Ukraine's ailing economy to recover.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese people's spectacular economic achievements reflect
the need for attaining political accord within the nation and
rallying all political forces around certain goals," Pustovoitenko
said.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine had been haunted by squabbles between the executive and
legislature for years. Political infighting was believed to be a
major factor hindering the country's recovery from the worsening
economic recession.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister stressed the importance of steady, clear-cut
and meaningful political and economic policies. He said: "China's
sober and predictable economic strategy makes the nation
attractive for foreign investors."
</P>
<P>
Besides praising his Chinese counterpart, Li Peng, for
channeling funds to promising and profitable enterprises,
Pustovoitenko said his visit to the Shenzhen Stock Exchange was
very instructive as to how to make Ukraine's stock exchanges
efficient, viable and booming.
</P>
<P>
"To make China's valuable experience of economic reforms
applicable and more adapted to Ukraine's realities, a Ukrainian
experts group will be sent to Shanghai shortly after the New Year
holidays," he said.
</P>
<P>
The group's mission would be to find out what should be done to
set up free economic zones in Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
