<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CIS's Industrial Output Up in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Industrial output of most
members of the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) in the
first 11 months this year showed a growth over the same period
last year, said a CIS statistics commission report on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Of the 12 CIS members, Kyrgyzstan enjoyed the highest growth of
49.1 percent. It was followed by Belarus and Georgia with 16.8
percent and 9.8 percent respectively, the Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Those also reporting increase are Uzebikstan, Kazakhstan,
Russia and Azerbaijan.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine, Moldova and Tajikistan, however, had declines of 1.8
percent, 2.2 percent and 5.1 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
As for the gross national product (GNP), Kyrgyzstan also took
first place with a growth of 11 percent. It was followed by
Belarus, Azerbaijan and Russia with 10 percent, 5.3 percent and
0.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Armenia's and Tajikistan's GNP in the January-October period
increased by 1.5 and 0.8 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's GNP in the first 11 months this year dropped four
percent from the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
