<HEADLINE> Maradona Ready to Return to Napoli </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Argentine soccer star Diego
Maradona is said to return to Italian Serie A side Napoli as a
player-manager, Italian news agency ANSA reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Neapolitan businessman and politician Nicola Rivelli is part of
a consortium hoping Maradona to be back to Napoli. Rivelli is
currently in talks with Napoli president Corrado Ferlaino for
buying the club.
</P>
<P>
"The important thing is that Diego has said...that he is ready
to return to Napoli and would do so once we have formalised our
offer to Ferlaino," said Rivelli, who was in Paris with Maradona's
representative Guillermo Coppola.
</P>
<P>
Maradona, who announced his retirement as a player two months
ago, was quoted as saying in Buenos Aires last week that he wanted
wide powers to try to bail out Napoli who are bottom of the
Italian first division.
</P>
<P>
Napoli completed a league and cup double in 1987, thanks
largely to Maradona's inspiration.
</P>
<P>
They went on to lift the UEFA Cup in 1989 and a second league
title in 1990 but have won nothing since the former Argentine
captain left the club in 1992. 
</P>
