<HEADLINE> Stoichkov Says Ronaldo Is Best </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Hristo Stoichkov, the Bulgarian
star striker at the 1994 World Cup, said he thought Brazil's
Ronaldo was the best soccer player in the world.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with BTA, Stoichkov said Ronaldo, who was
signed by Inter Milan from Barcelona last summer and plays well in
Brazil's national team, has a strong, even performance.
</P>
<P>
"Ronaldo is one of the best players in the world now, or maybe
I should say the best," said Stoichkov, who won the Golden Shoe in
the World Cup finals in the United States in 1994.
</P>
<P>
He said next year's World Cup finals in France would be a
tougher test for Bulgaria than the 1994 edition.
</P>
<P>
Stoichkov, who plays for Spainish club Barcelona, said in an
interview with BTA that his country must be better prepared but at
the same time not weighed down by the psychological burden.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian team must not be anxious because in the past few
years many of its players went abroad and gained experience, he
added.
</P>
<P>
"We must not worry at all. The teams playing against us must do
all the worrying. After all, we are the world's fourth strongest
team," Stoichkov said.
</P>
<P>
Summing up his work in 1997, helping Bulgaria to win a berth in
France was the most important task for Stoichkov and he was happy
that Barcelona topped the Spanish league rankings after the first
half of the season.
</P>
<P>
"This is the first time I have had an operation in my career
followed by a slow recovery. But everything is just fine,"
Stoichkov said.
</P>
<P>
"There are few cups I have not won. In 1997 we won the Cup
Winners' Cup, Spain's Cup and Super Cup. The only cups that we
failed to lift were the UEFA Cup and the Inter-Continental Cup
which we lost in Tokyo some years ago," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
