<HEADLINE> Most of Beijing Residents Use Gas for Cooking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- About 2.2 million households
in the Chinese capital, or 90 percent of the city's total, have
used natural gas for cooking.
</P>
<P>
Beijing residents started to use natural gas for cooking in the
late 1950s. However, natural gas supply can not meet the needs of
the residents, because residential construction in the city has
developed rapidly in recent years, with five million square meters
of floor space put into use annually.
</P>
<P>
Last September, natural gas was piped into Beijing from Shaanxi
and Gansu provinces and the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region in
northwest China, improving the supply.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Beijing municipal government said that by the
year 2000, Shaanxi, Gansu and Ningxia will pipe into Beijing 700
million cubic meters of natural gas a year. Then, all the Beijing
households will use natural gas for cooking.  
</P>
</TEXT>
