<HEADLINE> U.S. Reinsurance Company to Set up Office in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The New York-based
Transatlantic Reinsurance Company announced today that it will set
up a representative office in Shanghai, China, next year.
</P>
<P>
Company spokesman David Smith told reporters that the Bank of
China authorized the establishment of the office on October 29 and
the company is expected to see its office physically set up in
China's most populous city and economic center in February or
March.
</P>
<P>
The company's reinsurance program will cover property,
construction, engineering and other products, Smith said.
</P>
<P>
Robert Orlich, President and Chief Executive Officer of the
company said the new office will allow it to better serve
longstanding clients and create new opportunities in a rapidly
developing insurance market.
</P>
<P>
Transatlantic Reinsurance Company is a subsidiary of
Transatlantic Holdings, Inc. (TRH) which is a leading
international reinsurance organization with operations also based
in Toronto, Buenos Aires, London, Paris, Zurich, Hong Kong and
Tokyo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
