<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Shoot Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street shot
higher today, rekindling hopes for a year-end rally as many
traders returned from Christmas holidays.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 113.10 points to
7,792.41, pushing this year's gain back above 20 percent with just
two sessions to go.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by more than a 2-to-1 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with NYSE volume totaling 441.24
million shares, more than the combined tallies from Wednesday's
and Friday's shortened sessions.
</P>
<P>
Broader measures also rose sharply as investors searched for
bargains, betting that a January flood of new investment capital
will create enough demand to put Asia's economic troubles on the
market's back burner for a while.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 16.90 to 953.36, and
the NYSE composite index was up 7.89 to 501.49.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 26.07 points to 1,537.45, and
the American Stock Exchange composite index rose 5.52 669.29.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
