<HEADLINE> New York Stock Exchange to Ring out Record 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The New York Stock Exchange
will end this year's last trading day on Wednesday by releasing
3,000 balloons on floor to celebrate a record year, it said in a
press release today.
</P>
<P>
During the year, the NYSE has seen 275 companies listed,
bringing total listed companies to 3,056, including 343 companies
from 45 countries.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average hit a record high of 8259.31
points on August 6.
</P>
<P>
Up to December 23, a total of 131.5 billion shares had been
traded, up 26 percent from 104.6 billions shares in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Total transaction volume amounted to 5.7 trillion dollars, 39
percent or 1.6 trillion dollars higher than the 1996 performance.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE now has 206.6 billion shares available for trading
and a total global market capitalization of 11.2 trillion U.S.
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
