<HEADLINE> Daimler-Benz Reports Higher 2nd Half Operating Profit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest industrial
group Daimler-Benz today said its operating profit in the second
half of this year surpassed the 1.85 billion marks (1.04 billion
U.S. dollars) earned in the first six months.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, its operating profit amounted to 2.4 billion marks
(1.35 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the Stuttgart-based company said its sales in
1997 would reach 120 billion marks (67.55 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
All of the group's four main businesses performed better this
year, with carmaking continuing to be the most profitable
department. The company's car sales rose 14 percent to a record 52
billion marks (29.27 billion dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
